# Complete RFC 9218 Implementation Guide for curl

## Quick Reference: What Each File Does

| Component | File | Purpose |
|-----------|------|---------|
| **Option Definition** | `include/curl/curl.h` | Defines CURLOPT_H3_STREAM_PRIORITY enum and struct |
| **Data Storage** | `lib/urldata.h` | Stores priority in UserDefined struct |
| **Option Handler** | `lib/setopt.c` | Implements curl_easy_setopt() logic |
| **CLI Config** | `src/tool_cfgable.h` | CLI config structure fields |
| **CLI Parser** | `src/tool_getparam.c` | Parses --h3-priority CLI option |
| **CLI Executor** | `src/tool_operate.c` | Calls curl_easy_setopt() with parsed values |
| **HTTP/3 Backend** | `lib/vquic/curl_ngtcp2.c` | Sends Priority header in HTTP/3 |
| **Tests** | `tests/unit/unit_h3_priority.c` | Unit tests for the feature |

---

## File-by-File Implementation

### 1. include/curl/curl.h

**Location**: Before `CURLOPT_LASTENTRY` (line ~2213)

**Add Option Enum**:
```c
  /* set a specific client IP for HAProxy PROXY protocol header? */
  CURLOPT(CURLOPT_HAPROXY_CLIENT_IP, CURLOPTTYPE_STRINGPOINT, 323),

  /* Set HTTP/3 stream priority (RFC 9218) with urgency and incremental flag */
  CURLOPT(CURLOPT_H3_STREAM_PRIORITY, CURLOPTTYPE_OBJECTPOINT, 324),

  CURLOPT_LASTENTRY /* the last unused */
} CURLoption;
```

**Add Struct Definition** (after curl_easy_escape, around line 2250+):
```c
/* HTTP/3 Stream Priority (RFC 9218) */
struct curl_h3_stream_priority {
  unsigned char urgency;      /* 0-7, where 0 is highest priority */
  unsigned char incremental;  /* 0 or 1 - can be processed incrementally */
};
```

---

### 2. lib/urldata.h

**Location 1**: Modify `struct Curl_data_priority` (line ~1244)

Change from:
```c
struct Curl_data_priority {
#ifdef USE_NGHTTP2
  struct Curl_easy *parent;
  struct Curl_data_prio_node *children;
#endif
  int weight;
#ifdef USE_NGHTTP2
  BIT(exclusive);
#endif
};
```

To:
```c
struct Curl_data_priority {
#ifdef USE_NGHTTP2
  struct Curl_easy *parent;
  struct Curl_data_prio_node *children;
#endif
  int weight;
#ifdef USE_NGHTTP2
  BIT(exclusive);
#endif
#ifdef USE_HTTP3
  /* RFC 9218 HTTP/3 Extensible Priorities */
  unsigned char h3_urgency;      /* 0-7, 0=highest, 3=default */
  unsigned char h3_incremental;  /* boolean flag */
#endif
};
```

**Location 2**: Add fields to `struct UserDefined` (after line 1813)

Add after the priority struct:
```c
#ifdef USE_HTTP3
  /* RFC 9218 HTTP/3 stream priority */
  unsigned char h3_priority_urgency;      /* 0-7 for HTTP/3 */
  unsigned char h3_priority_incremental;  /* boolean for HTTP/3 */
#endif
```

---

### 3. lib/setopt.c

**Location**: Before `default:` case (line ~3173)

Add before the default case:
```c
  case CURLOPT_QUICK_EXIT:
    data->set.quick_exit = (0 != va_arg(param, long)) ? 1L:0L;
    break;

#ifdef USE_HTTP3
  case CURLOPT_H3_STREAM_PRIORITY:
    /*
     * Set HTTP/3 stream priority (RFC 9218) with urgency and incremental flag
     */
  {
    struct curl_h3_stream_priority *priority = va_arg(param, struct curl_h3_stream_priority *);

    if(!priority) {
      /* Reset to defaults */
      data->set.h3_priority_urgency = 3;      /* default urgency */
      data->set.h3_priority_incremental = 0;  /* default: non-incremental */
    } else {
      /* Validate urgency (0-7) */
      if(priority->urgency > 7)
        return CURLE_BAD_FUNCTION_ARGUMENT;

      data->set.h3_priority_urgency = priority->urgency;
      data->set.h3_priority_incremental = priority->incremental ? 1 : 0;
    }
    break;
  }
#endif

  default:
    /* unknown tag and its companion, just ignore: */
    result = CURLE_UNKNOWN_OPTION;
    break;
```

---

### 4. src/tool_cfgable.h

**Location**: End of `struct OperationConfig` (before closing brace)

Add:
```c
#ifdef USE_HTTP3
  /* RFC 9218 HTTP/3 stream priority */
  unsigned char h3_priority_urgency;
  unsigned char h3_priority_incremental;
#endif
```

---

### 5. src/tool_getparam.c

**Location 1**: Add to aliases array (around line 100)

Add near other HTTP3-related options:
```c
  {\"*@H3\", \"h3-priority\",              ARG_STRING},
```

**Location 2**: Add parsing logic in main parameter loop

In the parameter handling section (where other string options like "http-version" are parsed), add:

```c
#ifdef USE_HTTP3
      else if(strncasecompare(\"h3-priority\", 12, &p->name[i], arg_len)) {
        const char *priority_str = nextarg;
        if(!priority_str)
          return PARAM_MISSING_VALUE;

        /* Parse format: u=N[,i]
           Example: \"u=3\" or \"u=0,i\" */
        unsigned char urgency = 3;  /* default */
        unsigned char incremental = 0;  /* default */

        /* Parse urgency parameter */
        if(strncmp(priority_str, \"u=\", 2) == 0) {
          char *end;
          long val = strtol(priority_str + 2, &end, 10);
          if(val < 0 || val > 7) {
            warnf(global, \"Invalid urgency value (must be 0-7): %ld\\n\", val);
            return PARAM_BAD_USE;
          }
          urgency = (unsigned char)val;

          /* Check for incremental flag */
          if(*end == ',' && *(end+1) == 'i') {
            incremental = 1;
          }
        } else {
          warnf(global, \"Invalid priority format. Use: u=<0-7>[,i]\\n\");
          return PARAM_BAD_USE;
        }

        config->h3_priority_urgency = urgency;
        config->h3_priority_incremental = incremental;
      }
#endif
```

